  REQUIREMENTS

  - Meson 0.63 or later
  - Ninja build system
  - C compiler with C23 support (GCC 11+, Clang 13+, or later)
  - Tcl 8.5 or later (required)
  - Python 3.6+ (optional, for Python scripting support)

  Eggdrop bundles its own TLS library (opssl), so no external TLS
  library installation is needed. IPv6 support is always compiled in.

  A. Standard build process (Linux, FreeBSD, macOS, etc.)

  1. From the Eggdrop directory, configure the build:

       meson setup builddir

     Some common meson options:
       -Dtls=disabled        disable TLS support (not recommended)
       -Dmodule-python=true  enable Python scripting support
       -Dprefix=/custom/path install to a custom directory
       -Dbuildtype=debug     build with debug symbols for crash analysis

  2. Build Eggdrop:

       ninja -C builddir

  3. Install Eggdrop:

       ninja -C builddir install

     By default, this installs to ~/eggdrop. To install elsewhere, set
     the prefix during step 1 with -Dprefix=/desired/path.

  4. (Optional) Generate TLS certificates for your bot:

       cd ~/eggdrop
       make sslcert

     Or for non-interactive certificate generation:

       make sslsilent

  B. Advanced build options

  - List all available build options:

      meson configure builddir

  - Modify options after initial setup:

      meson configure builddir -Doption=value

  - Build with optimizations for a specific CPU:

      meson setup builddir -Dcpu_family=x86_64 -Dcpu=native

  C. Platform-specific notes

  Linux

    Eggdrop automatically detects and uses the most efficient I/O
    backend available:

      - io_uring (best performance, Linux 5.6+)
      - epoll (Linux 2.6+)
      - select() (portable fallback)

    No additional configuration is needed.

  macOS

    Eggdrop uses the kqueue I/O event backend on macOS, which provides
    efficient event-driven networking without the overhead of select().

    TLS is provided by opssl, which is bundled and built automatically.
    No external TLS library (such as OpenSSL) needs to be installed.

    If you need to install Tcl on macOS:

      brew install tcl-tk

    Make sure Meson can find Tcl by setting the PKG_CONFIG_PATH:

      export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=/usr/local/lib/pkgconfig:$PKG_CONFIG_PATH

  FreeBSD / OpenBSD / NetBSD

    Eggdrop uses the kqueue I/O backend on BSD systems for efficient
    event handling.

    Install required dependencies:

      pkg install meson ninja tcl

    Then follow the standard build process in Section A.

  Cygwin / Windows

    1. Download and install Cygwin (www.cygwin.com). Make sure to
       install the following packages: gcc, meson, ninja, tcl-devel,
       pkg-config.

    2. Extract the Eggdrop source:

         tar -zxf eggdrop-1.10.1.tar.gz
         cd eggdrop-1.10.1

    3. Build and install:

         meson setup builddir
         ninja -C builddir
         ninja -C builddir install DESTDIR=/your/install/path

  Cross-compilation

    To cross-compile Eggdrop, create a Meson cross file and pass it
    to meson setup:

      [binaries]
      c = 'arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc'
      ar = 'arm-linux-gnueabihf-ar'

      [properties]
      c_args = ['-march=armv7-a']
      c_link_args = ['-march=armv7-a']

    Then:

      meson setup builddir --cross-file=cross.ini

  D. Tcl detection and installation

    If Meson cannot automatically detect Tcl on your system, you can
    manually specify its location:

      meson setup builddir -Dtcl_include_path=/path/to/tcl/include \
        -Dtcl_lib_path=/path/to/tcl/lib

    To compile Tcl from source in your home directory:

      1. Download Tcl from https://www.tcl.tk/
      2. Extract and compile:

           tar -zxf tcl<VERSION>-src.tar.gz
           cd tcl<VERSION>/unix
           ./configure --prefix=$HOME/tcl
           make
           make install

      3. Configure Eggdrop to use your Tcl installation:

           export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/tcl/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
           meson setup builddir -Dtcl_include_path=$HOME/tcl/include \
             -Dtcl_lib_path=$HOME/tcl/lib

  E. Troubleshooting

  1. I get build warnings—is that a problem?

    Build warnings do not necessarily indicate problems. As long as the
    build completes successfully, there is nothing to worry about.
    However, if you encounter errors (not warnings), the build will fail.

  2. I get a compile error with C23 features

    Ensure your C compiler supports C23. Update your compiler:

      GCC:   version 11 or later
      Clang: version 13 or later

    If using an older compiler, update it before attempting to build
    Eggdrop.

  3. How do I enable/disable modules?

    During meson setup, specify which modules to build. For example, to
    disable the Python module:

      meson setup builddir -Dmodule-python=false

    List all available module options with:

      meson configure builddir | grep module-

  4. "Tcl not found" or "Could not find dependency Tcl with any of the
     specified package managers"

    Meson cannot detect Tcl on your system. Install Tcl development
    files:

      Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):
        apt-get install tcl-dev

      Linux (Fedora/RHEL):
        dnf install tcl-devel

      macOS:
        brew install tcl-tk

      FreeBSD:
        pkg install tcl

    Then try again. If it still fails, manually specify Tcl paths as
    described in Section D.

  5. "Meson" or "Ninja" not found

    Install Meson and Ninja:

      Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):
        apt-get install meson ninja-build

      Linux (Fedora/RHEL):
        dnf install meson ninja-build

      macOS:
        brew install meson ninja

      FreeBSD:
        pkg install meson ninja

  6. Permission denied when running ninja install

    If you do not have permission to write to the installation
    directory, use sudo:

      sudo ninja -C builddir install

    Or specify a different installation directory during setup:

      meson setup builddir --prefix=$HOME/eggdrop

